to the editor a federal appeals court 's ruling that a cleveland school voucher program violates the first amendment front page dec 12 need not doom school choice even if the united states supreme court ultimately concurs educational opportunity could be promoted immediately through broader tax relief be it across the board cuts or more targeted measures like increased child exemptions meaningful tax relief would provide all families with additional financial resources that they could use for their children 's education while avoiding the constitutional barriers that continue to impede progress on vouchers at the same time it would give families added flexibility to address other needs like health care coverage retirement savings and home mortgage payments donald sutherland white plains dec 12 2000 the writer is a research fellow institute for socioeconomic studies

